OL,3,COffering work experience 'too time
OL,4,Cconsuming', some businesses claim
OL,6,FPaul Whiteman, general secretary at
OL,7,Fschool leaders' union NAHT, said:
OL,8,F"School leaders recognise that work
OL,9,Fexperience and high-quality careers
OL,10,Fadvice are vital in helping young
OL,11,Fpeople plan for their future.
OL,13,F"However, simply expecting schools to
OL,14,Fdeliver work experience, without
OL,15,Fconsidering some of the systemic
OL,16,Fbarriers, including the capacity and
OL,17,Fbuy-in of businesses across the
OL,18,Fcountry, could leave the promise of
OL,19,Funiversal work experience out of
OL,20,Freach."
